
[1]poorly

   POOR'LY, adv. Without wealth; in indigence or want of the conveniences
   and comforts of life; as, to live poorly.

   1. With little or no success; with little growth, profit or advantage;
   as, wheat grows poorly on the Atlantic borders of New England; these
   men have succeeded poorly in business.

   2. Meanly; without spirit.

   Nor is their courage or their wealth so low,

   That from his wars they poorly would retire.

   3. Without excellence or dignity. He performs poorly in elevated
   characters.

    POOR'LY, a. Somewhat ill; indisposed; not in health; a common use of
                            the word in America.

   For three or four weeks past I have lost ground, having been poorly in
   health.
